<h1>Joseph Casabona</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://casabona.org/now/">casabona.org/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Scranton
PA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Front End Developer at Crowd Favorite. Published Author and an Adjunct Professor at The University of Scranton.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I build things on the web, and sometimes write about them.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Building websites lets me exercise both my logic and creativity. I love solving problems and then watching people use those solutions.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You should hope someone calls you a “freak” or a geek or a nerd. It shows you care about something enough for them to notice.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Masters of Doom by David Kushner
</p>

